long int factorial(int n) {
    if (n <= 1) {
        return 1;
    } else {
        return n * factorial(n-1);
    }
}
```

In this program, we define a function `factorial()` that takes an integer `n` as input and returns the factorial of `n`. In the main function, we call this function with `num` as argument (which is 5 in our case) and print the result using `printf()`. The long int data type is used to handle large factorials as factorials grow very quickly.
